Body: Date: Wed, 20 Nov 1996 22:11:18 GMT Server: NCSA/1.4.2 Content-type: text/html Last-modified: Tue, 03 Sep 1996 13:09:48 GMT Content-length: 907 Theory of Computation Theory of Computation (Computer Science 109) Times: 97W: Arrange Instructors: Young Prerequisite: Computer Science 45 and 49 This course explores the notion of computability restricted to a model of computation with one or more bounded resources (e.g., time or space).
